By: Râmâmâtya
---
The music which is called Gândharva (Mârga) is that which has been from time
immemorial, practised by the Gandharvas (celestial singers) and which leads
surely to Moksa (liberation), while the Gâna (Desi) music is that which has
been invented by composers.
